tonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 29, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nvg1719678978669.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nvg1719678978669.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nvg1719678978669.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qnp1665702754145\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /pkg\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the name of the Java package into which <code class=\"ph codeph\">/sto</code> should generate Java source files for Java call-in.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__section_w1125ab1b5b1_w1126ab1b5_w1127ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__p_d150647e1_d150648e1_d150649e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pkg</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">JavaPackage</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__section_w1128ab1b5b3_w1129ab1b5_w1130ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d536346e69\">\n                  \n Used With\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__d6208e20\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"grk1665702753295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/grk1665702753295.html\" title=\"Export interface definitions to integrate call-in from various types of middleware, or generate Java files for Java call-in, or generate C call-out stub code.\">/sto</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__section_w1131ab1b5b5_w1132ab1b5_w1133ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d536346e85\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__p_d150659e1_d150660e1_d150661e1\">When you use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sto</span> to generate Java files for Java call-in, you can use this subswitch to specify the full name of the Java package to contain the Java source files, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/sto /lan=jav /pkg=bank.account ...\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__p_d150662e1_d150663e1_d150664e1\">Note that the default behavior of <code class=\"ph codeph\">/sto /lan=jav ...</code> is to create Java packages (directories) named after the Uniface subsystems (except the subsystem Default) in which the Uniface signatures occur. If you also use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pkg</span>=<var class=\"keyword varname\">JavaPackage</var> subswitch, these subsystem package directories will be created under the <var class=\"keyword varname\">JavaPackage</var> directory.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnp1665702754145__p_d150665e1_d150666e1_d150667e1\">Assuming the signatures FData and MData occur in subsystems Father and Mother, respectively, the following command line creates Java source files in the directories <span class=\"ph filepath\">work/family/Father</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">work/family/Mother</span>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/sto /lan=jav /pth=work /pkg=family ExportFile FData MData\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422584\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422584\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/pkg Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 29, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /pkg Specify the name of the Java package into which /sto should generate Java source files for Java call-in. /pkg = JavaPackage Used With /sto Description When you use /sto to generate Java files for Java call-in, you can use this subswitch to specify the full name of the Java package to contain the Java source files, for example: /sto /lan=jav /pkg=bank.account ... Copy Note that the default behavior of /sto /lan=jav ... is to create Java packages (directories) named after the Uniface subsystems (except the subsystem Default) in which the Uniface signatures occur. If you also use the /pkg = JavaPackage subswitch, these subsystem package directories will be created under the JavaPackage directory. Assuming the signatures FData and MData occur in subsystems Father and Mother, respectively, the following command line creates Java source files in the directories work/family/Father and work/family/Mother : /sto /lan=jav /pth=work /pkg=family ExportFile FData MData Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}